=== 48857076 davedx ===
I switch between both as my daily drivers.

I do almost all my regular coding tasks with Codex 5.5 on medium.
Sometimes for niche edge cases, or when I run out of tokens on my Codex
sub, I'll switch to Claude. Some recent examples where Claude was able
to solve things Codex couldn't:

- 3D gamedev layout: I asked Codex to render a solar system in a certain
camera positioning, saying it needed to fit the planets of the system to
the viewport. Codex just couldn't do it, even on high reasoning: Claude
Opus did it first attempt.

- Tricky Tiptap image drag-n-drop layout implementation: Codex failed
this after numerous iterations. Claude Opus also struggled mightily to
get it to work, but I think around 3 attempts it nailed it. Both of them
ended up grepping the Tiptap code from node_modules - that's the kind of
task it was.

But these are really isolated examples. Across all my projects (I have
many; mostly TypeScript, but also things like C#), Codex "Just Works"
(tm), with minimal prompting effort from me.
