300M parameter model, [3mfour[0m orders of magnitude smaller than the
frontier).

[[31m1[m]: ]8;;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48464732[34mnews.ycombinator.com/item?id=48464732[m]8;;

Fortunately once you know how it works (i.e. dumb keyword classifier)
it's easy-ish to get around: just rename the keys so that it doesn't
contain the naughty keyword. (At least as long as it doesn't trigger on
something in its own thinking trace, which needs… more creative
workarounds.)
