=== 48862537 enraged_camel ===
Yes, this is exactly why I said yesterday that OpenAI does benchmaxxing,
seemingly quite a bit [[31m1[m]. I got a flurry of downvotes for it at first,
but I think people came around to it once they tried the model like you
did.

Ultimately I think the issue is that OpenAI is under tremendous pressure
to perform, but GPT-6 is not ready yet, so they had to push GPT-5 to its
limits, and the only way they could do it was with really heavy RLHF,
which has its shortcomings. Like, it is super obvious that Sol, Terra
and Luna are all heavily biased towards working on a problem
relentlessly because that's what their reward functions emphasized. That
pushes up their scores in some benchmarks but does not translate to
actual intelligence and capability.

